<section name="Welcome to Maven for PHP">
Maven for PHP uses the power of Maven for building, reporting on and creating documentations of PHP projects.
It adapts the Maven build lifecycle to the PHP world while fully supporting PHP 5.
PHP for Maven uses <a href="http://www.phpunit.de/" target="_blank"><b>PHPUnit</b></a> for unit testing and <a href="http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/" target="_blank"><b>doxygen</b></a> for creating the api documentation.
<br></br>Use a <b>PHP library project</b> to create a library that can be used by other PHP libraries or PHP web projects. Use a <b>PHP web project</b> to create a standalone web project. 

<p>
  <b>NOTICE:</b> PHP-Maven Version 1 is no longer supported. Visit <a href="migration-1x.html">the migration from Version 1 site.</a><br></br>
  Maven2 is no longer supported. We will need Maven3.<br></br>
</p>

